Citation.sAbstract: Viscosities were measured for the ternary systems Y(NO3)3 +  Ce(NO3)3 + H2O, Y(NO3)3 + Nd(NO3)3 + H2O, and Ce(NO3)3 + Nd(NO3)3 +  H2O and their binary subsystems Y(NO3)3 + H2O, Ce(NO3)3 + H2O, and  Nd(NO3)3 + H2O at (293.15, 298.15, and 308.15) K and atmospheric pressure.  The results were used to test the applicability of simple equations for the  viscosity of mixed solutions. The predictions agree well with measured values,  implying that the viscosities of the examined electrolyte solutions can be related  to those of their constituent binary solutions using these simple equations.
Citation.sTitle: Viscosities of the Ternary Systems Y(NO3)3 + Ce(NO3)3 + H2O, Y(NO3)3 +  Nd(NO3)3 + H2O, and Ce(NO3)3 + Nd(NO3)3 + H2O and Their Binary  Subsystems at Different Temperatures and Atmospheric Pressure
